As mentioned above, for the studied 2 projects and other super high-rise office buildings, the VAV systems were applied for a better indoor environment. Fig.6
                      illustrates the schematic diagram and control logic of the VAV system. For each VAV box, the supply air volume (Ga
                     ), the air damper opening (D), and the indoor air temperature of control area (Ti
                     ) are monitored. The control system of VAV boxes will calculate the air supply volume required (Ga,r
                     ) by comparing the actual Ti
                      with the setting value (Ti,s
                     ). Then, the D of VAV box is regulated to ensure the actual Ga
                      reaches the Ga,r
                     . Besides, there are often setting values of maximum and minimum Ga
                      for each VAV box; thus the actual Ga
                      is adjusted between Ga,

                     max and Ga,

                     min. With the D of each VAV box regulated, the static pressure (Pa
                     ) of the air flue is changed, then the operational frequency of fan (Fa
                     ) in AHU is regulated to ensure the actual Pa
                      to reach setting value, thus the total supply air volume of AHU (Ga,t
                     ) is regulated. In addition, the opening of water valve is regulated to ensure the supply air temperature (Tsa
                     ) to reach the setting value. Therefore, the setting values of supply air temperature (Tsa,s
                     ), static pressure (Pa,s
                     ), and Ga,

                     min would directly influence the energy performance of the VAV system, and the chilled water system.
